result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Joshua A. Baneck in court, in custody with Attorney Thomas J Laitsch.   ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.

On Count #1 of Case 15CF299:
The Court sentences Mr. Baneck  to  10  years of Imprisonment, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  4  years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 6  years.  This sentence is to commence FORTHWITH

The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 

On Count #2 of Case 15CF299 the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 5 year, to be served consecutive to Count #1

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision and Probation:
--random drug screening
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations

--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling  as required by the Agent
--
no possession of any dangerous weapon
--no presence at Hometown Pharmacy in Watertown, Wisconsin
--no contact with any known drug offenders unless authorized by agent or as part of ongoing treatment services
--to pay statutory court costs

--to pay court appointed attorney fees

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant

140 days credit to applied to Count #1

The Court finds that Mr. Baneck has already provided a DNA sample and does not order him to provide another sample
